          "name": "indexPaths",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "An array of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsindexpath"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " objects identifying the items you want to update."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To update the contents of existing (including prefetched) cells without replacing them with new cells, use this method instead of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uitableview/1614935-reloadrows"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". For optimal performance, choose to reconfigure rows instead of reloading rows unless you have an explicit need to replace the existing cell with a new cell."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Your cell provider must dequeue the same type of cell for the provided index path, and must return the same existing cell for a given index path. Because this method reconfigures existing cells, the table view doesn’t call "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uitableviewcell/1623223-prepareforreuse"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " for each cell dequeued. If you need to return a different type of cell for an index path, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uitableview/1614935-reloadrows"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instead."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If your cells are self-sizing, the table view resizes your cells after reconfiguring them."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default, the table view animates any size or layout changes that are a result of reconfiguration. To reconfigure cells without animation, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UIView"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiview/1622484-performwithoutanimation"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " when you call this method. Alternatively, to avoid animations when setting specific properties, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiview/1622484-performwithoutanimation"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in your cell configuration logic."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If your table view uses a custom implementation of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UITableViewDataSource"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", use this method. If your table view uses a diffable data source, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/nsdiffabledatasourcesnapshot/3804468-reconfigureitems"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " on "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSDiffableDataSourceSnapshot"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instead."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
